The hexagonal spiral is the usual “hex‑spiral” numbering.  
For a point \((q,r)\) in axial coordinates the ring number is  

\[
k=\max\{|q|,|r|,|\,(-q-r)\,|\}
\]

and the first number of that ring is  

\[
N_{\text{start}}=2+3k(k-1).
\]

For side 2 of the ring (all points with \(q=-k\)) the offset from the start of the ring is  

\[
m = 3k-r .
\]

Consequently the number at \((q,r)\) is  

\[
N = N_{\text{start}} + m .
\]

---

### Position of 2026

For 2026 the coordinates are \((-26,4)\); \(k=26\).  
Its offset is \(m = 3\cdot 26-4 = 74\), and indeed

\[
N = 2+3\cdot26\cdot25+74 = 2026.
\]

---

### The six neighbours

Adding the six hex‑neighbour directions to \((-26,4)\) gives the neighbour coordinates and their rings:

| neighbour | \((q,r)\) | ring \(k\) | side 2 | offset \(m\) | number |
|-----------|-----------|------------|--------|-------------|--------|
| 1 | \((-25,4)\) | 25 | yes | \(3\cdot25-4=71\) | \(1802+71=1873\) |
| 2 | \((-25,3)\) | 25 | yes | \(75-3=72\) | \(1802+72=1874\) |
| 3 | \((-26,3)\) | 26 | yes | \(78-3=75\) | \(1952+75=2027\) |
| 4 | \((-27,4)\) | 27 | yes | \(81-4=77\) | \(2108+77=2185\) |
| 5 | \((-27,5)\) | 27 | yes | \(81-5=76\) | \(2108+76=2184\) |
| 6 | \((-26,5)\) | 26 | yes | \(78-5=73\) | \(1952+73=2025\) |

---

### Sum of the six neighbour numbers

\[
\begin{aligned}
S &= 1873+1874+2025+2027+2184+2185 \\
  &= 3747 + 4052 + 4369 \\
  &= 12168 .
\end{aligned}
\]

\[
\boxed{12168}
\]
